   "source": [
    "#| label: johnson-relative-weights\n",
    "#| echo: true\n",
    "#| code-fold: false\n",
    "johnson_raw = johnson_relative_weights(X_z, y_z)\n",
    "\n",
    "johnson_pct = normalize_to_100(\n",
    "    johnson_raw,\n",
    "    use_absolute=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "display(Markdown(f\"Johnson's relative weights sum to **{johnson_raw.sum():.3f}**.\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "970135e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If Johnson's relative weights and Shapley values identify the same top drivers, that provides stronger evidence that those variables are important.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 10. Random forest mean decrease in Gini coefficient\n",
    "\n",
    "The final method uses a random forest classifier. Random forests can capture nonlinear relationships and interactions among predictors.\n",
    "\n",
    "The random forest importance measure used here is mean decrease in Gini impurity. A variable receives higher importance when it is frequently used in decision trees to create splits that improve classification purity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "random-forest-gini",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| label: random-forest-gini\n",
    "#| echo: true\n",
    "#| code-fold: false\n",
    "rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(\n",
    "    n_estimators=1000,\n",
    "    criterion=\"gini\",\n",
    "    max_features=\"sqrt\",\n",
    "    min_samples_leaf=5,\n",
    "    random_state=123\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_model.fit(X_raw, y_raw.astype(int))\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_gini_raw = rf_model.feature_importances_\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_gini_pct = normalize_to_100(\n",
    "    rf_gini_raw,\n",
    "    use_absolute=False\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
